Interface ResettableClassFileTransformer.Reset

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ResettableClassFileTransformer.Reset.Simple, ResettableClassFileTransformer.Reset.WithErrors
    Enclosing interface:
    ResettableClassFileTransformer

    public static interface ResettableClassFileTransformer.Reset
    A result of a class file transformer reset by a ResettableClassFileTransformer.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  ResettableClassFileTransformer.Reset.Simple
      A simple result without errors.
      static class  ResettableClassFileTransformer.Reset.WithErrors
      A result with a map of errors.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Map<Class<?>,Throwable> getErrors()
      Returns a mapping of classes that could not be reset to the errors occured when attempting the reset.
      boolean isApplied()
      Determines if this result did apply a deregistration, i.e. the reset class file transformer was not removed previously.

    • Method Detail

      • isApplied

        boolean isApplied()
        Determines if this result did apply a deregistration, i.e. the reset class file transformer was not removed previously.
        Returns:
        true if the represented reset was applied.

      • getErrors

        Map<Class<?>,Throwable> getErrors()
        Returns a mapping of classes that could not be reset to the errors occured when attempting the reset. If no errors occurred, this map is empty. This map is also empty, if this result is not alive.
        Returns:
        A map containing all errors that occured during a reset.
